vim setup
============================================

NERDTree
---
copy the zip content of NERDTree into ~/.vim/

.vimrc file
---
set number
syntax on
set tabstop=4
set shiftwidth=4
set autoindent
set expandtab
set softtabstop=4
set mouse=a
autocmd vimenter * NERDTree
let NERDTreeMapOpenInTab='<ENTER>'


HOWTO 
1. use mouse to jump to the editing area immediately 
2. use mouse to browse around in NERDTree 
3. use mouse to display the selected file
4. select NERDTree-dir, press "cd" as current workspace
5. use "ENTER" to open file in a new tab
6. use mouse or "gt" to switch among tabs
7. use "Ctrl+w" to switch among windows
8. use "i" for vertical split
9. Comment/uncomment
    -> ctrl+V choosing multiple lines
    -> shift+I, then type to comment
    -> ESC
    -> ctrl+V, press x to uncomment
